From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 08:50:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kati: resolve makefile read/include against
 Evaluator.working_dir
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First logical-cwd boundary. Makefile::from_file now takes (display_name,
open_path): it reads bytes from open_path but interns display_name for
Locs/$(MAKEFILE_LIST), so the resolved path never leaks into output. The
file_cache resolves the include/makefile name against the requesting
Evaluator's working_dir (absolute names pass through) and keys the cache by
that resolved absolute path — so two in-process makes in different directories
that both `include Makefile` get their own correct entries instead of
colliding, and the cache stays shareable.

Call sites (eval do_include, standalone main parse, engine katirun parse) pass
their Evaluator's working_dir. With working_dir == process cwd the resolved
path names the same file and the interned display name is identical, so
standalone rkati is byte-identical: KATI_COMPAT_PASS=364/378, fail=0. Engine
builds.

Remaining boundaries ($(wildcard)/$(abspath)/$(realpath)/$(file), find root)
follow the same shape.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
